	(362,70,'page_description',''),
	(363,70,'_page_description','field_56f0d08ab57b3'),
	(364,69,'page_description','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><img class=\"alignright wp-image-1124\" src=\"http://fourpointenergy.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/map-perspective-6-7.jpg\" alt=\"map-perspective-6-7\" width=\"553\" height=\"345\" />\r\nThe Anadarko Basin is one of the deepest sedimentary basins in North America. The basin has profitably produced hydrocarbons for over 100 years and has gone through many periods of revitalization as the technology and creative thinking of oil and gas extraction has evolved. In FourPointâs area of focus in the Western Anadarko Basin, 23 different correlative zones have been successfully targeted since 2005 and the start of the modern horizontal drilling revolution. From the relatively shallow and oil-bearing Douglas, Tonkawa and Cleveland sandstones, and down through 1,000âs of feet of increasingly gas-dominated Granite Wash reservoirs, this hydrocarbon province provides an incredible depth of opportunity.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">FourPointâs rigorous approach to geoscience and engineering, combined with our operational expertise and innovation has repeatedly allowed us to expand the known limits of the most prolific parts of these resource plays. As we continue to recognize and develop the best areas, we are building a consolidated, world-class asset and driving the next transformation of this time-tested basin.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The Permian Basin has more recently joined the list of basins revitalized by drilling and fracture stimulating horizontal wells, and now dominates the headlines. Covering such a large area with over 20 horizontal targets in the Midland and Delaware sub-basins, we are convinced our business model of technical excellence and business development expertise will provide us with opportunities to build consolidated positions and execute profitable operations.</p>'),
