	(733,65,'timeline_items_3_timeline_description','Prior to the sale of CEP II, the management team and CEPâs equity investors elected to form Cordillera Energy Partners III (CEP III), while still managing and operating CEP II so as not to lose momentum, opportunities, or talent. In March of 2007, CEP III was formed with a $500 million equity investment from EnCap Investments, along-side institutional investors and management. CEP III also entered into a $600 million, six bank credit facility again led by JP Morgan Chase.'),
