	(5817,702,'timeline_items_0_timeline_year','2000'),
	(5818,702,'_timeline_items_0_timeline_year','field_56fab9c610702'),
	(5819,702,'timeline_items_0_timeline_description','Cordillera Energy Partners was founded in February 2000 and incorporated as a Limited Liability Company formed in the state of Texas. The Company formed by George Solich, President and CEO, and his management team, employed the âacquire/exploitâ strategyâbuying producing assets and underdeveloped assets in three core areas. They enhanced production, cash flow, and reserves through a combination of drilling and lowering the cost structure, while adding additional âbolt-onâ acquisitions.'),
	(5820,702,'_timeline_items_0_timeline_description','field_56fab9e210703'),
	(5821,702,'timeline_items_0_timeline_image','129'),
	(5822,702,'_timeline_items_0_timeline_image','field_56fabab98eafe'),
	(5823,702,'timeline_items_1_timeline_year','2003'),
	(5824,702,'_timeline_items_1_timeline_year','field_56fab9c610702'),
	(5825,702,'timeline_items_1_timeline_description','The core areas for Cordillera Energy Partners I (CEP I) were the Anadarko Basin, the Delaware Basin and the San Juan Basin. Through a combination of acquisitions and drilling, CEP I grew its production to 30 MMCFED, annual cash flow to $35 million, and proved reserves to 250 BCFE by mid-2003. In October 2003, CEP I sold its assets to Patina Oil & Gas for cash and warrants to purchase Patina stock valued at $247 million.'),
	(5826,702,'_timeline_items_1_timeline_description','field_56fab9e210703'),
