	(7485,795,'timeline_items_2_timeline_year','2004'),
	(7486,795,'_timeline_items_2_timeline_year','field_56fab9c610702'),
	(7487,795,'timeline_items_2_timeline_description','Upon completion of the CEP I sale, the core management team formed CEP II, again with EnCap Investments, seven along-side institutional investors and management. In March of 2004, the company was capitalized with a $200 million private equity investment and a $300 million credit facility from six banks led by JP Morgan Chase. CEP II added to its management team ranks and set out to chart the same âacquire/exploitâ strategy that had been so successful in CEP I.'),
	(7488,795,'_timeline_items_2_timeline_description','field_56fab9e210703'),
