	(212,2,'2016-03-30 22:24:31','2016-03-30 22:24:31','There are many misunderstandings and false ideals about what oil and gas companies really do to produce clean, reliable energy for America. In fact, a large population of people donât really even think about how they themselves use energy outside of filling up the gas tank. For just a minute, step back and think about getting in your car, riding a bus, train, or plane, coming home and flipping on a light switch, turning on that fireplace, or the simple use of hot water. Those are all relatively common uses of energy, but have you ever thought about how that same energy, specifically energy from fossil fuels, is being used to make plastics, synthetic materials, TVâs, shoes, medicines, and even toothpaste? There are numerous other simple and far more complex examples we could toss out there, but the bottom line is each and every one of them use energy, specifically energy from fossil fuels.\r\n\r\nThere are many great educational websites, articles, and publications available for you to learn more about the industry, but more specifically for you to be able to make an accurate and educated opinion about the importance of this enormously valuable natural resources we have right here in America.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1225\" src=\"http://fourpointenergy.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/infograph_insideenergy.jpg\" alt=\"infograph_insideenergy\" width=\"1655\" height=\"870\" />\r\n\r\n<strong data-redactor-tag=\"strong\">Get the Facts:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Over 95% of wells are fracked during their lifespan.</li>\r\n 	<li>What is in Fracking Fluid? 99.5% of fracking fluid is water (90%) and sand (9.5%). 0.5% consists of common and safe chemical additives that are typically found in common household products.</li>\r\n 	<li>The fracking process was first used in 1947 and has been safely used ever since. The EPA has never found a connection to chemicals entering groundwater as a result of the fracking process.</li>\r\n 	<li>The use ofÂ natural gas isÂ criticalÂ for a majority ofÂ manufactures.Â 96%Â of products used by the general population on a daily basis contain components made with natural gas.</li>\r\n 	<li>Ethane a liquid derived from natural gas is a key building block for the creation of plastics and synthetic materials.</li>\r\n 	<li>The United StatesÂ isÂ the worldâs largest producer of oil and natural gas.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h5><em>Sources: U.S. Energy Information Administration, Coloradans Responsible for Energy Development (CRED), Energy from Shale, Energy In Depth</em></h5>\r\n<h5>[youtube id=\"dVim1GS302o\" align=\"center\" mode=\"normal\" autoplay=\"no\"]<em>Source: Chevron Corporation</em></h5>\r\n<h5>[youtube id=\"Y5hc8l_VPdk\"Â align=\"center\" mode=\"normal\" autoplay=\"no\"]<em>Source:Â ChevronÂ Corporation</em></h5>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong data-redactor-tag=\"strong\">âThe Moral Case for Fossil Fuelsâ - Alex Epstein</strong>\r\n\r\nAlex Epstein is the President and Founder of the <a href=\"http://industrialprogress.com/about/\">Center for Industrial Progress</a> (CIP), a for-profit think-tank and communications consulting firm focused on energy and environmental issues. CIP believes the keys to a new industrial revolution are a new industrial philosophy, a new industrial policy, and a new approach to communication. As a renowned philosopher, Alex has argued the case for fossil fuels by taking a big-picture, humanistic approach to industrial and environmental controversies.\r\n\r\n[youtube id=\"G86ut7zc1wI\"Â align=\"center\" mode=\"normal\" autoplay=\"no\"]\r\n<em data-redactor-tag=\"em\">Source: Center for Industrial Progress</em>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong data-redactor-tag=\"strong\">Information &amp; Educational Websites Links:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://www.cngnow.com\" target=\"_blank\">CNG Now</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://www.cred.org\" target=\"_blank\">Coloradoans for Responsible Energy Development</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://www.energyfromshale.org\" target=\"_blank\">Energy from Shale</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://www.anga.us\" target=\"_blank\">Americaâs Natural Gas Alliance</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://www.uncoverenergy.com\" target=\"_blank\">Uncovering North American Energy</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://www.energytomorrow.org\" target=\"_blank\">Energy Tomorrow</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://www.energyindepth.com\" target=\"_blank\">Energy In Depth</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://www.eia.gov\" target=\"_blank\">U.S. Energy Information Administration</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://www.bakerhughes.com\" target=\"_blank\">Baker Hughes</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong data-redactor-tag=\"strong\">Articles &amp; Publications:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://fourpointenergy.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/Foreign-Affairs-United-States-of-Gas.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">The United States of Gas</a> By: Robert Hefner</li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://fourpointenergy.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/The-Basics_Hydraulic-Fracturing.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">The Basics: Hydraulic Fracturing</a> By: COGA</li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://fourpointenergy.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/The-Basics_Drill-Time-Basics.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">The Basics: Drill Time Basics</a> By: COGA</li>\r\n</ul>','Oil & Gas Facts','','publish','closed','closed','','oil-gas-facts','','','2016-06-15 21:16:40','2016-06-15 21:16:40','',90,'http://fourpointenergy.com/?page_id=212',0,'page','',0),
