	(522,2,'2016-04-19 14:37:18','2016-04-19 14:37:18','<h3>Why lease or sell to FourPoint Energy?</h3>\r\n<h4><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-356\" src=\"http://fourpointenergy.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/fpo300x300.png\" alt=\"fpo300x300\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" />Aggressive Offers</h4>\r\nWe pay at or above market based terms and are experienced to move quickly on simple or complex trades.\r\n<h4>Defined Areas of Focus</h4>\r\nOur leasing is focused on areas where FourPoint actively drills and operates.\r\n<h4>Active Developer</h4>\r\nWe are not an asset warehouse. Our business strategy employs an acquisition development model that accelerates the pace of value creation.\r\n<h4>Financial Strength</h4>\r\nAs a privately funded company, we have a strong balance sheet with over $2.5 billion of committed capital and backing from some of the largest funds in private equity.\r\n<h4>Highly Experienced Team</h4>\r\nOur team of engineers, geologists, landman and other professionals have a strong experience base. We are committed to capturing valuable opportunities through adaptability, innovative thinking, and strategic relationships. This translates to being able to execute on leasing, drilling and acquisitions in the most efficient and effective manner.\r\n<h4>Experienced Vertical and Horizontal Driller</h4>\r\nWe have a dedicated team of drilling and completion engineers as well as development geologists that have drilled and completed over 320 operated wells in the last 16 years with nearly 200 of those in the modern horizontal environment.\r\n<h4>Active Producing Property Buyer</h4>\r\nWith over 30 years of demonstrated acquisition experience to evaluate and pay for producing and undeveloped reserves, FourPoint has closed over ___ acquisition transactions ranging in size from less than $1 million to $1 Billion.\r\n<h4>Responsible Operator</h4>\r\nWe are a prudent, responsible, low cost operator. We have a disciplined approach to efficiency and cost reduction. Our technical team is highly experienced in drilling and completions in both horizontal and vertical wells. We are committed to the safe and environmentally responsible development of our energy resources and invest time and resources to improve the communities in which we live and work.\r\n<h4>Relationship Driven</h4>\r\nOur acquisition strategy incorporates a win-win philosophy to deal making. We strive to build long-term relationships and partnerships that stimulate additional transactions down the road.\r\n<h4>Farmouts and Joint-Ventures</h4>\r\nWe encourage owners to provide us the opportunity to accelerate the development of their acreage via farmout or joint-venture agreements.\r\n<div class=\"opp-contact\">\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">Contact for Leasing</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Scott Haselwood</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Senior Land Advisor, Manager of Leasing\r\n(303) 785-1547 (direct)\r\n(303) 290-9997 (fax)\r\n(303) 720-877-1564 (cell)\r\nEmail: <a href=\"mailto:shaselwood@fourpointenergy.com\"><u data-redactor-tag=\"u\">shaselwood@fourpointenergy.com</u></a></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"opp-contact\">\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">Contact for Asset Sales</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Brad Marvin</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Vice President, Business Development\r\n(303) 785-1554 (direct)\r\n(303) 290-9997 (fax)\r\n(303) 974-0275 (cell)\r\nEmail: <a href=\"mailto:bmarvin@fourpointenergy.com\"><u data-redactor-tag=\"u\">bmarvin@fourpointenergy.com</u></a></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<h3>Main areas of focus for leasing and asset acquisitions</h3>\r\n<h4 class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">Active Plays:Â </span></h4>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\"><strong>Western Anadarko Basin:</strong> Texas Panhandle &amp; Western Oklahoma</span></p>\r\n\r\n<h4>Areas of Focus:</h4>\r\n<strong>New Mexico:Â </strong>Lea and Eddy\r\n\r\n<strong>Texas:Â </strong>Loving, Culberson, Winkler, Ward, Reeves, Martin, Howard, Glasscock, Midland, Upton, Reagan andÂ Operating Counties\r\n\r\n<strong>Texas:Â </strong>Hansford, Hemphill, Hutchinson, Lipscomb, Ochiltree, Roberts and Wheeler\r\n\r\n<strong>Oklahoma:Â </strong>Beckham, Blaine, Caddo, Canadian, Cleveland, Comanche, Custer, Dewey, Ellis, Garvin, Grady, McClain, Roger Mills, Washita and Woodward','Business Opportunities','','inherit','closed','closed','','71-revision-v1','','','2016-04-19 14:37:18','2016-04-19 14:37:18','',71,'http://fourpointenergy.com/2016/04/19/71-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
	(523,2,'2016-04-19 14:38:01','2016-04-19 14:38:01','<h3>Focus</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-356\" src=\"http://fourpointenergy.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/fpo300x300.png\" alt=\"fpo300x300\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" />\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Core areas with concentrated assets</li>\r\n	<li>Opportunities for organic growth and acquisition growth</li>\r\n	<li>Long life gas reserves in active plays and basins</li>\r\n	<li>High margin, repeatable plays driven by good geology, engineering, high margins, and strong upside</li>\r\n	<li>Growth in production, cash flow, and reserves</li>\r\n	<li>Focus Areas: Western Anadarko and Permian Basins</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3>People and Culture</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-356\" src=\"http://fourpointenergy.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/fpo300x300.png\" alt=\"fpo300x300\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" />\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Practicing and living out company values and behaviors (hyperlink to values)</li>\r\n	<li>A results driven culture of opportunistic, performance-driven, and goal-oriented employees/partners</li>\r\n	<li>Experts in core areas by fine tuning the geologic/engineering model</li>\r\n	<li>Creative and adaptive to an always changing environment</li>\r\n	<li>Deliberate and selective - Building a team of âAâ players</li>\r\n	<li>Develop a strong planâ execute on the plan; stay focused and do it again and again</li>\r\n	<li>Dedicated to value creation with a sense of urgency</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3>Organic Oriented Growth</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-356\" src=\"http://fourpointenergy.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/fpo300x300.png\" alt=\"fpo300x300\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" />\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Become the lessee of choice in each core area by doing what we said weâd do â be good stewards of the land and create value for our shareholders, landowners, royalty owners and communities in which we work</li>\r\n	<li>Build concentrated areas of leasehold to pursue a multi-rig drilling program to maximize efficiency and lessen delays in production and reserve growth</li>\r\n	<li>Emphasize geographic areas with quality production and reserve targets</li>\r\n	<li>Strive for win-win negotiations with landowners and surface owners to maximize the benefit to each party while mitigating the impact of our operations on the environment</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3>Acquire &amp; Exploit Oriented Growth</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Aggressively pursue the purchase of producing properties in our core areas when we can capture additional upside opportunities, acquire additional leasehold, lower costs, and increase production and cash flow</li>\r\n	<li>Develop and build relationships, deliver results, make more deals</li>\r\n	<li>Pursue unsolicited and pre-emptive offers on assets that we can be an aggressive buyer</li>\r\n	<li>Evaluate and pursue only those competitive transactions where we have a distinctive competence which will make us the most competitive buyer</li>\r\n	<li>Be efficient and effective at multiple evaluations</li>\r\n	<li>Stay in the market at all times as a buyer and seller</li>\r\n	<li>Achieve critical mass in each core area through consistent growth in reserves, production, and cash flow</li>\r\n	<li>Aggressively exploit upside opportunities</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Financial Flexibility</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Seek strong, flexible, patient and market-savvy equity partners</li>\r\n	<li>Preserve enough capital to weather dramatic changes in commodity prices</li>\r\n	<li>Maintain a strong relationship with commercial banks to utilize debt as a meaningful, but fiscally prudent, part of the capital structure</li>\r\n	<li>Seek hedging opportunities that help to secure expenditures on drilling and underpin acquisition economics</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>The Franchise Concept</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Build great asset bases with strong production, cash flow, and upside opportunities</li>\r\n	<li>Gain critical mass within 48 to 60 months and pursue the sale of assets to growth oriented, quality focused exploration and production enterprises</li>\r\n	<li>Grow the next enterprise in the same geographic region with the same technical expertise</li>\r\n	<li>Become the top consolidator of a large resource base characterized by, focused, geographically concentrated, technically delineated, high-quality assets with strong production and cash flow, and enormous growth of potential of undeveloped reserves.</li>\r\n</ul>','Business Strategy','','inherit','closed','closed','','78-revision-v1','','','2016-04-19 14:38:01','2016-04-19 14:38:01','',78,'http://fourpointenergy.com/2016/04/19/78-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
