	(526,2,'2016-04-19 14:41:13','2016-04-19 14:41:13','<img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-356\" src=\"http://fourpointenergy.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/fpo300x300.png\" alt=\"fpo300x300\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" />\r\n\r\nThere are many misunderstandings and false ideals about what oil and gas companies really do to produce energy for America. In fact a large population of people donât really even think about how they themselves even use energy outside of filling up the gas tank. For just a minute, step back and think about getting in your car, riding a bus, train, or plane, coming home and flipping on a light switch, turning on that fireplace, or the simple use of hot water. Those are all relatively common uses of energy but have you ever thought about how that same energy, specifically energy from fossil fuels is being used to make plastics, synthetic materials, TVâs, shoes, medicines, and even toothpaste? There are numerous other simple and far more complex examples we could toss out there, but the bottom line is each and every one of them use energy, specifically energy from fossil fuels.\r\n\r\nThere are many great educational websites, articles, and publications available for you to learn more about the industry, but more specifically for you to be able to make an accurate and educated opinion about the importance of this enormously valuable natural resources we have right here in America.\r\n\r\n<strong data-redactor-tag=\"strong\">Alex Epstein âThe Moral Case for Fossil Fuelsâ Video Link</strong>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-343\" src=\"http://fourpointenergy.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/fpo800x450.png\" alt=\"fpo800x450\" width=\"800\" height=\"450\" />\r\n\r\n<strong data-redactor-tag=\"strong\">Get the Facts:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Example 1</li>\r\n	<li>Example 2</li>\r\n	<li>Example 3</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong data-redactor-tag=\"strong\">Information &amp; Educational Websites Links:</strong>\r\n\r\n<img cl