	(733,2,'2016-05-05 19:08:06','2016-05-05 19:08:06','While success in business and being the best is always at the forefront of the FourPoint organization, giving back provides the balance the team needs to remain focused. FourPoint Energy values Compassionate Stewardship by striving to positively impact the lives of employees, partners, landowners, and shareholders by caring for and about people, communities, assets and performance.\r\n\r\nThe team at FourPoint takes pride in being able to give back and make a difference in peoplesâ lives, not only within the communities where employees live and work, but also on a national and global level. <del data-redactor-tag=\"del\"></del>FourPoint demonstrates support and community involvement in a variety of ways, from sponsored golf tournaments, luncheons, charitable donations, adopt-a-family programs, and numerous sponsored events within their operating communities.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-343\" src=\"http://fourpointenergy.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/fpo800x450.png\" alt=\"fpo800x450\" width=\"800\" height=\"450\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nFourPoint Energy believes in taking an active role for supporting local initiatives. The company is an active member of the:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>The Quarterly Forum</li>\r\n 	<li>Kynd Hub</li>\r\n 	<li>Canadian Chamber of Commerce</li>\r\n 	<li>Wheeler Chamber of Commerce</li>\r\n 	<li>Cheyenne - Roger Mills Chamber of Commerce</li>\r\n 	<li>Elk City Chamber of Commerce</li>\r\n 	<li>Canadian Rodeo</li>\r\n 	<li>Arnett Rodeo</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<em>âWe appreciate being part of the business community in the Texas Panhandle and Western Oklahoma. Our sponsorship and volunteer support of community groups and events is a small way to show our support for the communities where we live and workâ</em> â George Solich, President &amp; CEO','Community Engagement','','inherit','closed','closed','','215-revision-v1','','','2016-05-05 19:08:06','2016-05-05 19:08:06','',215,'http://fourpointenergy.com/2016/05/05/215-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
	(734,2,'2016-05-05 19:10:25','2016-05-05 19:10:25','<img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-356\" src=\"http://fourpointenergy.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/fpo300x300.png\" alt=\"fpo300x300\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" />\r\n\r\nThere are many misunderstandings and false ideals about what oil and gas companies really do to produce energy for America. In fact a large population of people donât really even think about how they themselves even use energy outside of filling up the gas tank. For just a minute, step back and think about getting in your car, riding a bus, train, or plane, coming home and flipping on a light switch, turning on that fireplace, or the simple use of hot water. Those are all relatively common uses of energy but have you ever thought about how that same energy, specifically energy from fossil fuels is being used to make plastics, synthetic materials, TVâs, shoes, medicines, and even toothpaste? There are numerous other simple and far more complex examples we could toss out there, but the bottom line is each and every one of them use energy, specifically energy from fossil fuels.\r\n\r\nThere are many great educational websites, articles, and publications available for you to learn more about the industry, but more specifically for you to be able to make an accurate and educated opinion about the importance of this enormously valuable natural resources we have right here in America.\r\n\r\n<strong data-redactor-tag=\"strong\">Alex Epstein âThe Moral Case for Fossil Fuelsâ Video Link</strong>\r\n\r\n[youtube id=\"G86ut7zc1wI\" align=\"center\" mode=\"normal\" autoplay=\"no\"]\r\n\r\n<strong data-redactor-tag=\"strong\">Get the Facts:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Over 95% of wells are fracked during their lifespan.</li>\r\n 	<li>What is in Fracking Fluid? -99.5% of fracking fluid is water (90%) and sand (9.5%). 0.5% consists of common and safe chemical additives that typically common household products.</li>\r\n 	<li>The fracking process was first used in 1947 and has been safely used ever since. The EPA has never found a connection to chemicals entering groundwater as a result of the fracking process.</li>\r\n 	<li>Natural Gas is a major component to manufactures. 95% of products used by the general population on a daily basis contain components made with Natural Gas.</li>\r\n 	<li>Ethane a liquid derived from Natural Gas is a key building block for the creation of plastics and synthetic materials</li>\r\n 	<li>America is now the worldâs largest producer of oil and natural gas.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong data-redactor-tag=\"strong\">Information &amp; Educational Websites Links:</strong>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-356\" src=\"http://fourpointenergy.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/fpo300x300.png\" alt=\"fpo300x300\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" />\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://www.cngnow.com\">CNG Now</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://www.cred.org\">Coloradoans for Responsible Energy Development</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://www.energyfromshale.org\">Energy from Shale</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://www.anga.us\">Americaâs Natural Gas Alliance</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://www.uncoverenergy.com\">Uncovering North American Energy</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://www.energytomorrow.org\">Energy Tomorrow</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://www.energyindepth.com\">Energy In Depth</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://www.eia.gov\">U.S. Energy Information Administration</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://www.bakerhughes.com\">Baker Hughes</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong data-redactor-tag=\"strong\">Articles &amp; Publications:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>The United States of Gas By: Robert Hefner</li>\r\n 	<li>The Basics: Well to Wheel By: COGA</li>\r\n 	<li>The Arc of History By: J.P. Morgan</li>\r\n 	<li>Worldwide Energy Fact Sheet By: (Source TBD â Brent working on)</li>\r\n</ul>','Inside Energy','','inherit','closed','closed','','212-revision-v1',''