nt balance is under $100.00?</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Please submit a request in writing with the dollar amount you would like to have revenue checks mailed to you. Please submit this request to <a href=\"mailto:ownerrelations@fourpointenergy.com\">ownerrelations@fourpointenergy.com</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>When can I expect to receive my 1099?</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Your 1099 will be mailed to you no later than January 31st. Please allow 10 business days after January 31st before contacting us regarding not receiving your 1099.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>What should I do if my check is lost or stolen?</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Please allow 10 business days after checks are mailed to receive your check. If after 10 business days you have still not received your revenue check please contact us at:\r\n<strong>(303) 785-1581</strong>\r\n<strong>Email:Â </strong><a href=\"mailto:ownerrelations@fourpointenergy.com\">ownerrelations@fourpointenergy.com</a></li>\r\n 	<li>If your check is stolen please contact us at:\r\n<strong>(303) 785-1581</strong>\r\n<strong>Email:Â </strong><a href=\"mailto:ownerrelations@fourpointenergy.com\">ownerrelations@fourpointenergy.com</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>How do I get a copy of my revenue check or joint interest billing?</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>To receive your User ID and password to <a href=\"https://www.energylink.com/\" target=\"_blank\">EnergyLink</a>, please contact us at:\r\n<strong>(303) 785-1581\r\n</strong><strong>Email:</strong> Â <a href=\"mailto:ownerrelations@fourpointenergy.com\">ownerrelations@fourpointenergy.com</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Why did you send me an IRS Form W-9?</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>The IRS requires that we confirm your Tax ID number every year and keep the <a href=\"http://fourpointenergy.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/FourPoint_W9.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">W-9</a> on file. Please complete the form using the name provided on your revenue check, and your Social Security number or Tax ID number.</li>\r\n</ul>','FAQ','','inherit','closed','closed','','514-revision-v1','','','2016-06-16 20:51:31','2016-06-16 20:51:31','',514,'http://fourpointenergy.com/514-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
	(1286,1,'2016-06-20 18:58:43','2016-06-20 18:58:43','This list provides the documentation FourPoint Energy will need in order to complete a change to your ownership account. All change requests must be submitted in writing.\n\nShould you have any additional questions regarding the documentation required to complete a change to your account, please feel free to <a href=\"http://fourpointenergy.com/contact-us/\">contact us</a>:\n\n<strong>(303) 785-1581</strong>\n<strong>Email:Â </strong><a href=\"mailto:ownerrelations@fourpointenergy.com\">ownerrelations@fourpointenergy.com</a>\n<h3><strong>Address Change</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n 	<li><a href=\"http://fourpointenergy.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ADDRESS-VERIFICATION_CHANGE-FORM-2016.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Submit request in writing</a> with your signature</li>\n 	<li>New <a href=\"http://fourpointenergy.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/FourPoint_W9.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">W-9</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>Appointment of Attorney-In-Fact</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n 	<li>Copy of Power of Attorney</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>Bankruptcy â Chapter 7</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n 	<li>Recorded conveyance (if applicable)</li>\n 	<li>Order naming trustee of bankruptcy estate</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>Bankruptcy â Chapter 11</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n 	<li>Plan of reorganization</li>\n 	<li>Order confirming the plan of reorganization</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>Changes in Trustee</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n 	<li>Instrument by which the Successor Trustee was appointed</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>Company Name Change</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n 	<li>Certificate of NameÂ Change including Tax I.D.</li>\n 	<li>New <a href=\"http://fourpointenergy.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/FourPoint_W9.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">W-9Â </a></li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>Change Due to Merger</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n 	<li>Certificate of Merger including Tax I.D.</li>\n 	<li>New <a href=\"http://fourpointenergy.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/FourPoint_W9.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">W-9</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>Death of owner with a will with probate proceedings conducted in the state where the property is located</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n 	<li>Death Certificate</li>\n 	<li>Letters testamentary</li>\n 	<li>Final decree of distribution or judgment of possession</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>Death of owner with a will with probate proceedings conducted outside the state where the property is located</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n 	<li>Death Certificate</li>\n 	<li>Letters testamentary</li>\n 	<li>Final decree of distribution or judgment of possession recorded in the county where the property is located</li>\n 	<li>Documentation of ancillary probate proceedings opened in all affected states</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>Death of owner without a will</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n 	<li>Death Certificate</li>\n 	<li>Letters of administration</li>\n 	<li>Final decree of distribution or judgment of possession recorded in the county where the property is located</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>Enroll or change in revenue direct deposit</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n 	<li>Submit <a href=\"http://fourpointenergy.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/FourPoint_DirectDepositEnrollment2016-with-mailing-info.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">new direct deposit form</a> with voided check</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>Joint Tenancy with Death of One Tenant</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n 	<li>Death Certificate of deceased tenant Life Estate â Death</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>Life tenantâs Death Certificate</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n 	<li>Names and addresses of remaindermen</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>Name Change</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n 	<li>Marriage Certificate or Divorce Decree reinstating maiden name or other legal document of name change</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>Ownership Change Due to Divorce</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n 	<li>Complete Divorce Decree including Settlement Agreement and recorded conveyances (if applicable)</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>Sale of Interest</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n 	<li>Complete copy of conveyance document filed of record in the county which the property is located</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>Trust or Partnership Creation or Dissolution</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n 	<li>Trust or Partnership Agreement and recorded conveyance(s) (if applicable)</li>\n</ul>\n<strong><em>Legal Advice</em></strong>\n\nFourPoint Energy is unable to provide legal advice. Please contact an attorney for any questions regarding legal advice.\n\n<strong><em>IRS Form W-9</em></strong>\n\nFederal law requires all owners to provide their social security number or tax identification number via an IRS Form <a href=\"http://fourpointenergy.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/FourPoint_W9.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">W-9</a>. Should you fail to provide this information, you may become subject to non-refundable backup withholding.\n<ul>\n 	<li>one</li>\n 	<li>two</li>\n</ul>','Change of Ownership','','inherit','closed','closed','','197-autosave-v1','','','2016-06-20 18:58:43','2016-06-20 18:58:43','',197,'http://fourpointenergy.com/197-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
	(1287,1,'2016-06-20 20:09:46','2016-06-20 20:09:46','<h3>The FourPoint Mission:\r\nTo Create Value That Makes A Difference</h3>\r\nFourPoint is primarily focused on acquiring and developing oil and natural gas assets in the Western Anadarko and Permian Basins. Founded by the leadership team of Cordillera Energy Partners following the sale to Apache Corporation in 2012, FourPoint Energy is proud to boast an exceptional team of professionals with over 30 years of industry-leading experience.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1022\" src=\"http://fourpointenergy.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/WhoWeAre.jpg\" alt=\"WhoWeAre\" width=\"1200\" height=\"500\" />\r\n\r\nFourPoint is committed to our mission of <strong data-redactor-tag=\"strong\"><em data-redactor-tag=\"em\">creating value that makes a difference</em></strong>. We strive to do this every day and in every part of the organization by fostering relationships with our investors, partners, land and mineral owners, vendors and employees with the highest level of respect and integrity. We are focused on continuous improvement through collaboration and innovation but also emphasize processes to maximize efficiencies.\r\n\r\nFourPoint is very proud of the culture and environment it has developed over the years. We are a dedicated team of individuals committed to carrying out our mission through six core values:\r\n<h3>Shared Vision</h3>\r\nCreating an organization of people who share a long-term perspective driven to create value and enhance their quality of life.\r\n<h3>Committed Teamwork</h3>\r\nFostering a respectful and inclusive environment to collaborate across functions, embracing the talents of individuals and trusting one another to make the best decisions.\r\n<h3>Empowering People</h3>\r\nEntrusting our people with responsibility and authority while making them accountable to our mission, values, and goals.\r\n<h3>Driven to Excellence</h3>\r\nCommitting to deliberate and continuous improvement and striving to be the best with passion, integrity and humility.\r\n<h3>Entrepreneurial</h3>\r\nCapturing valuable opportunities through adaptability, innovative thinking and strategic relationships.\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3>[youtube id=\"kDolQlZWSmw\" align=\"center\" mode=\"normal\"]</h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3>Compassionate Stewardship</h3>\r\nPositively impacting the lives of our employees, partners, landowners, and shareholders by caring for and about people, communities, assets and performance.\r\n<h3></h3>','Who We Are','','inherit','closed','closed','','67-revision-v1','','','2016-06-20 20:09:46','2016-06-20 20:09:46','',67,'http://fourpointenergy.com/67-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
